# ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# <type>(<scope>): <concise subject –- 50 chars max, no period>
#
# • type  : feat | fix | docs | refactor | perf | test | chore | ci
# • scope : folder/module or ticket ref (optional)
#
# Leave an empty line after the subject!
#
########  Why (context / problem)  ###########################################
#
#   – What problem or requirement does this change address?
#
########  What (solution / changes)  #########################################
#
#   – Bullet-point summary of the user-visible changes.
#   – Mention any removed or deprecated behaviour.
#
########  How (implementation notes)  #######################################
#
#   – Key design decisions, algorithms, tricky bits worth future reading.
#   – Flags, env vars, or config files touched.
#
########  Testing ############################################################
#
#   – Test steps performed or automated tests added/updated.
#   – State “N/A” if not applicable (but ideally never leave empty).
#
########  Security / Compliance ##############################################
#
#   – New permissions, ports, secrets, or CVE fixes?  Y/N + details.
#
########  Docs / Ticket refs ##################################################
#
#   – Links to Jira/GitHub issues, Confluence pages, RFCs, etc.
#
########  Footers #############################################################
#
# Signed-off-by: Your Name <you@example.com>
# Reviewed-by:   <optional reviewers>
# Co-authored-by: <optional pair-programmer>
#
# ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
